  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Mechanical Technician",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Descriptions:</strong></u></p><p>• Manage emergency/ unscheduled repairs of production equipment. Provide redesign and improvements to equipment</p><p>• Subject Matter Expert (SME) on Root Cause Failure Analysis (RCFA) and ensure action follow-up to prevent recurrence of breakdowns.</p><p>• Lead repairs, improvement project implementation and liaise with vendors / contractors on scope of work.</p><p>• Lead Root Cause Analyses (RCA), conduct investigation, create solutions and take full ownership of the report, including coordinating/ follow-up investigation with team member.</p><p>• Lead spare parts Management and annual inventory stock-count.</p><p>• Compile and monitor Equipment Reliability Action Tasks execution and completion then analyze and optimize.</p><p>• Any other duties and responsibilities as assigned by the Maintenance Manager from time to time.</p><p><u><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></u></p><p>• Diploma/ Degree in mechanical Engineering or any relevant trade certificate.</p><p>• Minimum 05 years of experience in a process plant with maintenance experience.</p><p>• Should be able to communicate in English written & spoken.</p><p>• Knowledge of mechanical / process systems.</p><p>• Able to work independently as well as in a team with strong troubleshooting skill.</p>",
